<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en" class="scroll-smooth dark" data-theme="dark">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
    <title>SeaRei - ML Hybrid System Technical Documentation</title>
    <script src="https://cdn.tailwindcss.com"></script>
    <style>
        @import url('https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Inter:wght@300;400;500;600;700;800;900&family=JetBrains+Mono:wght@400;500;600&display=swap');
        
        * {
            font-family: 'Inter', -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, sans-serif;
            -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased;
        }
        
        code, pre, .mono {
            font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace;
        }
        
        .gradient-bg {
            background: linear-gradient(135deg, #667eea 0%, #764ba2 100%);
        }
        
        .gradient-text {
            background: linear-gradient(135deg, #667eea 0%, #764ba2 100%);
            -webkit-background-clip: text;
            -webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
            background-clip: text;
        }
        
        .code-block {
            background: #1e1e1e;
            border-radius: 8px;
            padding: 16px;
            overflow-x: auto;
        }
        
        .card {
            transition: all 0.3s cubic-bezier(0.4, 0, 0.2, 1);
        }
        
        .card:hover {
            transform: translateY(-2px);
            box-shadow: 0 10px 30px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.15);
        }
        
        /* Dark mode overrides for ChatGPT-like feel */
        /* ChatGPT-like Dark Mode Palette */
        :root {
            --accent: #10A37F; /* OpenAI green */
            --link: #4EA4F4;
        }
        :root.dark, .dark {
            --bg: #202123;       /* page background */
            --panel: #343541;    /* navbar/header panel */
            --card: #2A2B32;     /* content cards */
            --text: #ECECF1;     /* primary text */
            --muted: #ACB2C1;    /* secondary text */
            --code: #1E1F22;     /* code block bg */
            --code-border: #3A3D41;
        }
        /* Containers */
        .dark body { background-color: var(--bg) !important; color: var(--text); }
        .dark nav.bg-white { background-color: var(--panel) !important; }
        .dark .bg-white { background-color: var(--card) !important; }
        .dark .bg-gray-50 { background-color: var(--bg) !important; }
        .dark .gradient-bg { background: var(--panel) !important; }
        .dark .border { border-color: #3b3f4a !important; }
        .dark .shadow-sm { box-shadow: 0 1px 2px rgb(0 0 0 / 0.5); }
        /* Typography */
        .dark .text-gray-800, .dark .text-gray-700, .dark .text-black { color: var(--text) !important; }
        .dark .text-gray-600, .dark .text-gray-500, .dark .text-gray-400 { color: var(--muted) !important; }
        .dark a { color: var(--link); }
        /* Code blocks */
        .dark .code-block { background: var(--code); border: 1px solid var(--code-border); }
        /* Buttons / badges */
        .dark .bg-emerald-400 { background-color: var(--accent) !important; color: #0b0b0b !important; }
        .dark .hover\:bg-emerald-300:hover { background-color: #2ac69c !important; }
        /* Nav links */
        .dark nav a { color: #E5E7EB !important; }
        .dark nav a:hover { color: #A78BFA !important; }
        /* Force no light backgrounds in dark mode */
        .dark .bg-white, .dark .bg-gray-100, .dark .bg-gray-200, .dark .bg-gray-300,
        .dark .bg-blue-50, .dark .bg-green-50, .dark .bg-red-50, .dark .bg-purple-50,
        .dark .bg-white\/20, .dark .bg-white\/30, .dark .bg-white\/40,
        .dark [class*="bg-white/"], .dark [class*="bg-gray-50"],
        .dark [class*="bg-blue-50"], .dark [class*="bg-green-50"],
        .dark [class*="bg-red-50"], .dark [class*="bg-purple-50"] {
            background-color: var(--card) !important;
        }
        .dark .text-white { color: var(--text) !important; }
        .dark .bg-white\/20 { background-color: rgba(255,255,255,0.08) !important; }
        .dark .hover\:bg-white\/30:hover { background-color: rgba(255,255,255,0.12) !important; }
        .dark .border-l-4 { border-color: #3b3f4a !important; }
        .dark .rounded-lg, .dark .card { background-color: var(--card) !important; }
        .dark header.gradient-bg { box-shadow: inset 0 -1px 0 rgba(255,255,255,0.04); }

        /* OpenAI-style Dark — semantic tokens */
        :root[data-theme="dark"] {
          /* Surfaces */
          --bg-app:        #343541;
          --bg-surface:    #444654;
          --bg-sidebar:    #202123;
          --bg-input:      #40414F;
          --bg-hover:      #2A2B32;
          --bg-active:     #3A3B46;

          /* Borders */
          --border-muted:  #565869;
          --border-subtle: #2C2D35;

          /* Text */
          --text-primary:   #ECECF1;
          --text-secondary: #C5C7D0;
          --text-muted:     #9AA0A6;
          --text-invert:    #0B0C10;

          /* Accent & states */
          --accent-brand:   #10A37F;
          --accent-brand-2: #A970FF;
          --accent-focus:   #2BB397;
          --success:        #1DB954;
          --warning:        #F59E0B;
          --error:          #EF4444;
          --info:           #38BDF8;

          /* Selection / scroll / shadow */
          --selection-bg:     #3B3D4A;
          --scrollbar-thumb:  #3A3B46;
          --scrollbar-track:  #232429;
          --shadow-ambient:   0 6px 24px rgba(0,0,0,.35);

          /* Code */
          --code-bg:         #1E1E2E;
          --code-border:     #2C2D3A;
          --code-inline-bg:  #2A2B3B;
          --code-text:       #E6E8EE;

          --syntax-keyword:  #A970FF;
          --syntax-string:   #86D993;
          --syntax-number:   #F59E0B;
          --syntax-fn:       #7DD3FC;
          --syntax-comment:  #6B7280;
          --syntax-op:       #EAB308;
        }

        /* Apply semantic tokens when html has data-theme=dark or class=dark */
        .dark body { background: var(--bg-app) !important; color: var(--text-primary) !important; }
        .dark nav.bg-white { background: var(--bg-surface) !important; }
        .dark header.gradient-bg { background: var(--bg-surface) !important; }
        .dark .bg-white, .dark .bg-gray-50 { background: var(--bg-surface) !important; }
        .dark .border { border-color: var(--border-subtle) !important; }
        .dark .text-gray-800, .dark .text-gray-700, .dark .text-black { color: var(--text-primary) !important; }
        .dark .text-gray-600, .dark .text-gray-500, .dark .text-gray-400 { color: var(--text-secondary) !important; }
        .dark a { color: var(--accent-brand) !important; }
        .dark a:hover { color: var(--accent-brand-2) !important; }
        .dark .code-block { background: var(--code-bg) !important; border: 1px solid var(--code-border); color: var(--code-text); }
        .dark pre, .dark code { background: var(--code-bg) !important; color: var(--code-text) !important; border-color: var(--code-border) !important; }
        .dark code.inline { background: var(--code-inline-bg) !important; border-radius: 6px; padding: .15rem .35rem; }
        .dark ::selection { background: var(--selection-bg); }
        .dark ::-webkit-scrollbar { width: 10px; height: 10px; }
        .dark ::-webkit-scrollbar-thumb { background: var(--scrollbar-thumb); border-radius: 8px; }
        .dark ::-webkit-scrollbar-track { background: var(--scrollbar-track); }
        .dark .shadow-sm, .dark .card { box-shadow: var(--shadow-ambient); }
        .dark input, .dark textarea { background: var(--bg-input) !important; color: var(--text-primary) !important; border: 1px solid var(--border-muted) !important; }
        .dark .bg-emerald-400 { background-color: var(--accent-brand) !important; color: var(--text-invert) !important; }
        .dark .hover\:bg-emerald-300:hover { background-color: var(--accent-focus) !important; }
        .dark .text-xs { color: var(--text-secondary) !important; }

        /* PrismJS-like token mapping */
        .dark .token.keyword   { color: var(--syntax-keyword); }
        .dark .token.string    { color: var(--syntax-string); }
        .dark .token.number    { color: var(--syntax-number); }
        .dark .token.function  { color: var(--syntax-fn); }
        .dark .token.operator  { color: var(--syntax-op); }
        .dark .token.comment   { color: var(--syntax-comment); }
        .dark pre[class*="language-"] {
          background: var(--code-bg) !important;
          color: var(--code-text) !important;
          border: 1px solid var(--code-border) !important;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body class="bg-gray-50 dark:bg-gray-900">
    <!-- Header -->
    <header class="gradient-bg text-white py-16">
        <div class="container mx-auto px-6 flex items-start justify-between">
            <div>
                <h1 class="text-5xl font-bold mb-4">SeaRei Multi-Tier AI Safety System</h1>
                <p class="text-xl opacity-90">Rules + Classical ML + Transformer + AEGIS: Complete Technical Documentation</p>
                <div class="mt-6 flex gap-4 text-sm flex-wrap">
                    <span class="bg-white/20 px-3 py-1 rounded">Version 2.1.0</span>
                    <span class="bg-white/20 px-3 py-1 rounded">159K Training Examples</span>
                    <span class="bg-white/20 px-3 py-1 rounded">2-6ms Avg Latency</span>
                    <span class="bg-white/20 px-3 py-1 rounded">77% F1 Score</span>
                    <span class="bg-white/20 px-3 py-1 rounded">97.6% ROC-AUC</span>
                    <a href="#aegis" class="px-3 py-1 rounded bg-emerald-400 text-black font-semibold hover:bg-emerald-300 transition">🛡️ AEGIS ENABLED</a>
                    <span class="px-3 py-1 rounded bg-green-500 text-white font-semibold">🤖 TRANSFORMER READY</span>
                </div>
            </div>
            <button id="themeToggle" class="mt-2 bg-white/20 hover:bg-white/30 text-white text-sm px-3 py-2 rounded transition">
                Toggle Dark Mode
            </button>
        </div>
    </header>

    <!-- Navigation -->
    <nav class="bg-white shadow-sm sticky top-0 z-50">
        <div class="container mx-auto px-6 py-4 flex gap-6 text-sm font-medium overflow-x-auto">
            <a href="#overview" class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300 hover:text-purple-600 whitespace-nowrap">Overview</a>
            <a href="#purpose" class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300 hover:text-purple-600 whitespace-nowrap">Purpose</a>
            <a href="#demo" class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300 hover:text-purple-600 whitespace-nowrap">Live Demo</a>
            <a href="#features" class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300 hover:text-purple-600 whitespace-nowrap">Features</a>
            <a href="#architecture" class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300 hover:text-purple-600 whitespace-nowrap">Architecture</a>
            <a href="#training" class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300 hover:text-purple-600 whitespace-nowrap">Training</a>
            <a href="#hybrid-system" class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300 hover:text-purple-600 whitespace-nowrap">Hybrid System</a>
            <a href="#aegis" class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300 hover:text-purple-600 whitespace-nowrap">AEGIS</a>
            <a href="#testing" class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300 hover:text-purple-600 whitespace-nowrap">Testing</a>
            <a href="#benchmarks" class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300 hover:text-purple-600 whitespace-nowrap">Benchmarks</a>
            <a href="#security" class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300 hover:text-purple-600 whitespace-nowrap">Security</a>
            <a href="#monitoring" class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300 hover:text-purple-600 whitespace-nowrap">Monitoring</a>
            <a href="#competitive" class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300 hover:text-purple-600 whitespace-nowrap">Competitive</a>
            <a href="#datasets" class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300 hover:text-purple-600 whitespace-nowrap">Datasets</a>
            <a href="#evidence" class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300 hover:text-purple-600 whitespace-nowrap">Evidence</a>
            <a href="#api" class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300 hover:text-purple-600 whitespace-nowrap">API Usage</a>
            <a href="#deployment" class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300 hover:text-purple-600 whitespace-nowrap">Deployment</a>
            <a href="#roadmap" class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300 hover:text-purple-600 whitespace-nowrap">Roadmap</a>
            <a href="#references" class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300 hover:text-purple-600 whitespace-nowrap">References</a>
        </div>
    </nav>

    <div class="container mx-auto px-6 py-12">
        
        <!-- Overview -->
        <section id="overview" class="mb-16">
            <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-6">System Overview</h2>
            
            <div class="bg-white p-8 rounded-lg shadow-sm mb-8">
                <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-4">Multi-Tier Hybrid Architecture: Rules + Classical ML + Transformer</h3>
                <p class="text-gray-700 mb-6">SeaRei uses a three-tier hybrid system that combines regex rules, classical ML (NB+LogReg), and a lightweight transformer (BERT-Tiny). This layered approach delivers both speed (2-6ms avg) and high accuracy (77% F1, 97.6% ROC-AUC).</p>
                
                <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-4 gap-4 mt-6">
                    <div class="border rounded-lg p-6">
                        <div class="text-purple-600 font-bold text-2xl mb-2">2-6ms</div>
                        <div class="text-sm text-gray-600">Average Latency</div>
                        <div class="text-xs text-gray-500 mt-2">Rules: 1.8ms, ML: 0.9ms, Transformer: 2-6ms</div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="border rounded-lg p-6">
                        <div class="text-purple-600 font-bold text-2xl mb-2">77%</div>
                        <div class="text-sm text-gray-600">F1 Score</div>
                        <div class="text-xs text-gray-500 mt-2">Transformer model on Jigsaw dataset</div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="border rounded-lg p-6">
                        <div class="text-purple-600 font-bold text-2xl mb-2">97.6%</div>
                        <div class="text-sm text-gray-600">ROC-AUC</div>
                        <div class="text-xs text-gray-500 mt-2">Excellent discrimination capability</div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="border rounded-lg p-6">
                        <div class="text-purple-600 font-bold text-2xl mb-2">18MB</div>
                        <div class="text-sm text-gray-600">Transformer Size</div>
                        <div class="text-xs text-gray-500 mt-2">100x smaller than full BERT</div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

        <!-- Purpose -->
        <section id="purpose" class="mb-16">
            <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-6">Purpose</h2>
            <div class="bg-white p-8 rounded-lg shadow-sm">
                <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">SeaRei is an AI Safety platform designed to reliably detect, explain, and continuously improve defenses against harmful content across modalities. It combines <strong>policy-as-code</strong>, a <strong>rules+ML hybrid guard</strong>, and an <strong>adaptive Adversarial Immune System (AEGIS)</strong> to protect users and enterprises in real time.</p>
                <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 text-gray-700">
                    <li><strong>Reliability:</strong> Sub‑10ms latency targets, high precision/recall tradeoffs.</li>
                    <li><strong>Explainability:</strong> Transparent decisions with rationales and metrics.</li>
                    <li><strong>Adaptivity:</strong> AEGIS learns from novel attacks and shares antibodies.</li>
                    <li><strong>Compliance & Auditability:</strong> Evidence and provenance for enterprise/regulators.</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
        </section>

        <!-- Features -->
        <section id="features" class="mb-16">
            <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-6">Platform Features (A–Z)</h2>
            <div class="bg-white p-8 rounded-lg shadow-sm">
                <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
                    <div class="border rounded-lg p-6">
                        <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-3">AEGIS (Adaptive Defense)</h3>
                        <ul class="text-gray-700 text-sm space-y-1">
                            <li>• Detects obfuscated/novel attacks; generates antibodies (regex patterns).</li>
                            <li>• Clonal selection keeps high‑fitness defenses; export/import for network effect.</li>
                            <li>• Basis: Artificial Immune Systems; entropy/obfuscation heuristics (sources in References).</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div class="border rounded-lg p-6">
                        <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-3">Hybrid Guard (Rules + ML)</h3>
                        <ul class="text-gray-700 text-sm space-y-1">
                            <li>• Parallel rules and ML; confidence‑aware fusion (weighted/threshold logic).</li>
                            <li>• ML: TF‑IDF + NB‑weighted Logistic Regression (6 labels, Jigsaw dataset).</li>
                            <li>• Sources: Wang & Manning 2012 (NB‑LR), Jigsaw Kaggle dataset.</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div class="border rounded-lg p-6">
                        <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-3">Policy‑as‑Code</h3>
                        <ul class="text-gray-700 text-sm space-y-1">
                            <li>• YAML policies with categories, patterns, safe contexts, thresholds.</li>
                            <li>• Hot reload; versioning and checksums; audit headers (X‑Policy‑*).</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div class="border rounded-lg p-6">
                        <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-3">Evidence & Provenance</h3>
                        <ul class="text-gray-700 text-sm space-y-1">
                            <li>• Model artifact hash (SHA‑256), training metadata, reproducible commands.</li>
                            <li>• Scorecards and telemetry bundles for audits and regressions.</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div class="border rounded-lg p-6">
                        <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-3">Monitoring & SLOs</h3>
                        <ul class="text-gray-700 text-sm space-y-1">
                            <li>• <span class="mono">/metrics</span> (Prometheus): latency histograms, request totals, circuit events.</li>
                            <li>• <span class="mono">/healthz</span>: build/policy status; request logs with request‑id and policy checksum.</li>
                            <li>• Targets: p50 &lt; 3ms, p99 &lt; 12ms; error rate &lt; 0.1%.</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div class="border rounded-lg p-6">
                        <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-3">Security & Compliance</h3>
                        <ul class="text-gray-700 text-sm space-y-1">
                            <li>• Least‑privilege tokens, rate limiting, circuit breakers, CORS hardening.</li>
                            <li>• FedRAMP/ISO27001 control alignment (logging, secrets, SBOM, evidence packs).</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

        <!-- Architecture -->
        <section id="architecture" class="mb-16">
            <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-6">ML Model Architecture</h2>
            
            <div class="bg-white p-8 rounded-lg shadow-sm mb-8">
                <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-4">Naive Bayes + Logistic Regression</h3>
                
                <div class="mb-6">
                    <h4 class="font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-3">Why This Architecture?</h4>
                    <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 text-gray-700">
                        <li><strong>Speed:</strong> 0.3-0.9ms inference (100x faster than transformers)</li>
                        <li><strong>Size:</strong> 2.6MB model (vs 400MB+ for BERT)</li>
                        <li><strong>Interpretability:</strong> Feature weights are explainable</li>
                        <li><strong>Production-ready:</strong> No GPU required, CPU-only</li>
                        <li><strong>Cost:</strong> $0 training cost on laptop</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>

                <div class="code-block mb-6">
                    <pre class="text-green-400 text-sm"><code># Model Pipeline
Input Text
    ↓
TF-IDF Vectorization (15,000 features, 1-2 grams)
    ↓
Naive Bayes Feature Weighting
    log(P(feature|toxic) / P(feature|safe))
    ↓
Weighted TF-IDF Features
    ↓
Logistic Regression (6 classifiers)
    - toxic
    - severe_toxic
    - obscene
    - threat
    - insult
    - identity_hate
    ↓
Output: Probability scores [0-1] per category</code></pre>
                </div>

                <div class="mb-6">
                    <h4 class="font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-3">Technical Details</h4>
                    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
                        <div class="border-l-4 border-purple-600 pl-4">
                            <div class="font-semibold">TF-IDF Vectorizer</div>
                            <ul class="text-sm text-gray-600 mt-2 space-y-1">
                                <li>• Features: 15,000 (optimized for speed)</li>
                                <li>• N-grams: 1-2 (captures phrases)</li>
                                <li>• Min DF: 3 (filter rare words)</li>
                                <li>• Max DF: 0.9 (filter common words)</li>
                                <li>• Sublinear TF: Yes (log scaling)</li>
                            </ul>
                        </div>
                        <div class="border-l-4 border-purple-600 pl-4">
                            <div class="font-semibold">Logistic Regression</div>
                            <ul class="text-sm text-gray-600 mt-2 space-y-1">
                                <li>• Solver: LBFGS (fast convergence)</li>
                                <li>• C: 4 (regularization)</li>
                                <li>• Max iter: 100 (quick training)</li>
                                <li>• Multi-class: 6 independent classifiers</li>
                                <li>• Training time: ~3 min on CPU</li>
                            </ul>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="bg-white p-8 rounded-lg shadow-sm">
                <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-4">NEW: Transformer Model (BERT-Tiny)</h3>
                <p class="text-gray-700 mb-6">Recently added: A lightweight transformer for cases requiring deeper semantic understanding. Trained locally on Apple Silicon MPS in 40 minutes.</p>
                
                <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 mb-6">
                    <div class="border-l-4 border-green-600 pl-4">
                        <div class="font-semibold mb-2">Model Specs</div>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                            <li>• <strong>Architecture:</strong> BERT-Tiny (prajjwal1/bert-tiny)</li>
                            <li>• <strong>Parameters:</strong> 4.4M (tiny compared to 184M for DeBERTa)</li>
                            <li>• <strong>Model size:</strong> 18MB</li>
                            <li>• <strong>Training time:</strong> 40 minutes (Apple Silicon M-series)</li>
                            <li>• <strong>Training cost:</strong> $0 (local training)</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div class="border-l-4 border-green-600 pl-4">
                        <div class="font-semibold mb-2">Performance Metrics</div>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                            <li>• <strong>ROC-AUC:</strong> 0.976 (97.6%)</li>
                            <li>• <strong>PR-AUC:</strong> 0.882 (88.2%)</li>
                            <li>• <strong>F1 Score:</strong> 0.772 (77.2%)</li>
                            <li>• <strong>MCC:</strong> 0.748 (74.8%)</li>
                            <li>• <strong>Inference:</strong> 2-6ms (after warmup)</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="bg-green-50 border-l-4 border-green-600 p-4">
                    <div class="font-semibold text-green-900 mb-2">Why BERT-Tiny?</div>
                    <div class="text-sm text-green-800">
                        <p class="mb-2">BERT-Tiny strikes the perfect balance for production deployment:</p>
                        <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-1">
                            <li>100x smaller than full BERT (18MB vs 400MB+)</li>
                            <li>10x faster inference (2-6ms vs 50-150ms)</li>
                            <li>Trains locally on consumer hardware (no cloud GPU needed)</li>
                            <li>Captures semantic nuance missed by classical ML</li>
                            <li>Source: BERT-Tiny by prajjwal1 (HuggingFace), trained on Jigsaw 159K examples</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
